.TH "pmcraid_reset_reload" 9 "pmcraid_reset_reload" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pmcraid_reset_reload \- utility routine for doing IOA reset either to bringup or bringdown IOA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pmcraid_reset_reload
.BI "(struct pmcraid_instance *pinstance "  ","
.BI "u8 shutdown_type "  ","
.BI "u8 target_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pinstance" 12
pointer adapter instance structure
.IP "shutdown_type" 12
shutdown type to be used NONE, NORMAL or ABRREV
.IP "target_state" 12
expected target state after reset
.SH "NOTE"
This command initiates reset and waits for its completion. Hence this
should not be called from isr/timer/tasklet functions (timeout handlers,
error response handlers and interrupt handlers).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return Value
1 in case ioa_state is not target_state, 0 otherwise.
